Responsibilities
- Design and implement software of embedded devices and systems from requirements to production and commercial deployment
- Design, develop, code, test and debug system software.

Requirements
- Bachelor/Diploma in Engineering (Computer/Telecommunication), Engineering (Electrical/Electronic) or equivalent.
- Minimum 4 years of experience in embedded software development using C, in RTOS environment.
- Understand the microcontroller architecture, Object Oriented Design (OOD) and multi-tasking software design on a RTOS/Embedded OS.
- Possess skills in any of the following would be advantageous:

  Knowledge of USB, Bluetooth technologies
  Knowledge of Audio and Video code
  Knowledge of CD/DVD/VCD implementation and standards
  Using JTAG/in-circuit emulator
  Design or work with software messaging/communication protocols

- Team player as well as ability to work independently.